            <title>[GROOVY-4440] Groovy Console looking for wrong LAF on Snow Leopard</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-4440</link>
                <project id="12318123" key="GROOVY">Groovy</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The Groovy Console is looking for the wrong LAF on Snow Leopard and not using the OS/X LAF as a result. The code is checking for &apos;apple.laf.AquaLookAndFeel&apos; but the LAF was moved to &apos;com.apple.laf.AquaLookAndFeel&apos;. The switch statement is in groovy.ui.ConsoleView.groovy but I assume groovy.ui.view.MacOSXDefaults.groovy and groovy.ui.view.MacOSXMenuBar.groovy will also need to be updated.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
